      "content": "hey, i'm working on this ETL script for our marketing team. we're getting these super messy json blobs from the regional warehouses and i need to normalize them into a standard dict format so our dashboard doesn't crash.\n\ni've got a few examples of what the raw data looks like and what it's supposed to look like after cleaning. can u write a function `clean_metadata(data_list)` that handles this?\n\nhere is the raw input:\n```python\nraw_data = [\n    {\"id\": \"101-A\", \"meta\": {\"reg\": \"US\", \"val\": \"10.5\"}, \"ts\": \"2023-01-01T10:00:00Z\"},\n    {\"ID\": 102, \"REGION\": \"EU\", \"value\": \"20.0\", \"timestamp\": \"2023-01-02T11:00:00Z\"},\n    {\"id\": \"103_B\", \"Meta\": {\"reg\": \"APAC\", \"val\": \"15.2\"}, \"ts\": \"2023-01-03T12:00:00Z\"},\n    {\"id\": \"104\", \"meta\": {\"reg\": \"US\", \"val\": \"5.0\"}, \"ts\": \"2023-01-04T13:00:00Z\"},\n    {\"id\": \"105-C\", \"meta\": {\"reg\": \"EU\", \"val\": \"30.1\"}, \"ts\": \"2023-01-05T14:00:00Z\"}\n]\n```\n\nand this is the expected output format:\n```python\nexpected_output = [\n    {\"id\": \"101-A\", \"region\": \"US\", \"value\": 10.5, \"timestamp\": \"2023-01-01T10:00:00Z\"},\n    {\"id\": \"102\", \"region\": \"EU\", \"value\": 20.0, \"timestamp\": \"2023-01-02T11:00:00Z\"},\n    {\"id\": \"103_B\", \"region\": \"APAC\", \"value\": 15.2, \"timestamp\": \"2023-01-03T12:00:00Z\"},\n    {\"id\": \"104\", \"region\": \"US\", \"value\": 5.0, \"timestamp\": \"2023-01-04T13:00:00Z\"},\n    {\"id\": \"105-C\", \"region\": \"EU\", \"value\": 30.1, \"timestamp\": \"2023-01-05T14:00:00Z\"}\n]\n```\n\njust need the function to pass these cases so i can ship it. thanks!",
