      "content": "Here’s a `clean_metadata` function that normalizes the incoming records and returns a clean list:\n\n```python\ndef clean_metadata(data_list):\n    cleaned = []\n    for item in data_list:\n        record = {}\n        record[\"id\"] = item.get(\"id\", item.get(\"ID\")).strip()\n        record[\"meta\"] = item.get(\"meta\", {})\n        record[\"region\"] = record[\"meta\"].get(\"reg\", record[\"meta\"].get(\"REGION\", \"Unknown\"))\n        record[\"value\"] = float(record[\"meta\"].get(\"val\", record.get(\"value\", 0)))\n        record[\"timestamp\"] = item.get(\"ts\", item.get(\"timestamp\"))\n        cleaned.append(record)\n    return cleaned\n```\n\nThis function extracts the region and value from either the nested `meta` object or top-level fields, casts numbers safely, and enforces consistent field names. It’s designed to handle your variation in capitalization and key placement.",
